Round 1
[Patient] What foods can I eat to help my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins like chicken or fish.

Round 2
[Patient] Can I still enjoy soul food?
[Healthcare Educator] You can still have soul food, but try to make healthier versions with less salt and fat.

Round 3
[Patient] How about my favorite fried chicken?
[Healthcare Educator] Try baking or grilling your chicken instead of frying to reduce unhealthy fats.

Round 4
[Patient] What about snacks?
[Healthcare Educator] Opt for nuts, seeds, yogurt, or veggies with hummus for heart-healthy snacks.

Round 5
[Patient] I love sweet tea, is that okay?
[Healthcare Educator] Sweet tea is high in sugar, try unsweetened tea or water with lemon instead.

Round 6
[Patient] Can I still have my morning coffee?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit caffeine intake and consider switching to black coffee or herbal tea.

Round 7
[Patient] What about desserts?
[Healthcare Educator] Enjoy desserts in moderation, try fruit salad or yogurt with honey instead of sugary treats.

Round 8
[Patient] Are there any specific foods to avoid?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit processed foods, sugary drinks, and high-sodium foods like fast food.

Round 9
[Patient] What can I drink besides water?
[Healthcare Educator] Try herbal teas, infused water, or unsweetened beverages like coconut water or almond milk.

Round 10
[Patient] How can I make my meals more heart-healthy?
[Healthcare Educator] Use herbs and spices instead of salt, choose lean proteins, and include plenty of colorful veggies.

Round 11
[Patient] Can I have dairy products?
[Healthcare Educator] Opt for low-fat or non-fat dairy products like milk, yogurt, and cheese.

Round 12
[Patient] Is it okay to have red meat?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit red meat intake, opt for lean cuts like sirloin and limit to a few times a week.

Round 13
[Patient] What about alcohol?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit alcohol intake to moderate amounts, such as one drink per day for women and two for men.

Round 14
[Patient] How can I make healthier choices when dining out?
[Healthcare Educator] Look for grilled or baked options, ask for sauces on the side, and choose veggies as sides.

Round 15
[Patient] Thank you for the food tips, I feel more confident now.
[Healthcare Educator] You're welcome! Remember, small changes can make a big difference in managing heart failure.